article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 59, Wichita St. 50
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Jhamar Youngblood scored 14 of his 17 points in the second half to lead Monmouth to a 59-50 victory over Wichita State on Saturday night at the Paradise Jam. Youngblood scored nine of his points during a 16-2 run that put the Hawks ahead 40-33 with 8:08 left. Monmouth (1-3), which suffered a 76-33 loss to Notre Dame in the first round of the tournament a day earlier, also got 17 points from Whitney Coleman and nine from Alex Nunner. Gal Meker led Wichita State (1-2) with 17 points and Phillip Thomasson added 16. The Shockers jumped out to a 12-2 lead on a driving layup by Matt Braeuer with 13:05 to play in the first half. But Monmouth rallied to tie the game at 18 when Alex Nunner found Whitney Coleman for a layup in heavy traffic with 1:50 to go before halftime. The Hawks opened the second half by taking their first lead on a 3-pointer by Youngblood that put them ahead 23-22. After the Hawks' big run, the Shockers rallied to cut the deficit to 42-40 on a layup by Thomasson with 4:18 to play but could not get any closer.
